cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper is about simplified LSTM recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP), speech recognition, and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which covers research on neural networks and their applications. The paper also discusses the performance of the models, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers research on algorithms and models for machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of LSTM in NLP and image processing, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
